        {
            "_id": "yCeYAoltBjTFyYoI",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/TwoActions.webp",
            "name": "Light Reflection",
            "sort": 900000,
            "system": {
                "actionCategory": {
                    "value": "offensive"
                },
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 2
                },
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Requirements</strong> The gold defender is not in darkness</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The gold defender reshapes its skin into a reflective surface that magnifies ambient light into a precise beam that burns all creatures in a @Template[type:cone|distance:30], dealing [[/r 14d6[fire]]] damage (@Check[type:reflex|dc:31|name:Light Reflection in Dim Light|traits:fire,damaging-effect] save if the gold defender is in dim light, @Check[type:reflex|dc:33|name:Light Reflection in Bright Light|traits:fire,damaging-effect] save if it's in bright light). It can't use Light Reflection again for [[/br {1d4} #rounds]]{1d4 rounds}.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature takes no damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature takes half damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature takes full damage and catches fire, taking [[/r {1d6}[persistent,fire] #Persistent Fire Damage]]{1d6} @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Persistent Damage]{Persistent Fire Damage}.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As failure, but the persistent fire damage is [[/r {5d6}[persistent,fire] #Persistent Fire Damage]]{5d6}.</p>"
